🧾 Problem Statement (Short + Example)

You are given:

numBottles = number of full water bottles initially
numExchange = number of empty bottles needed to get 1 new full bottle

You can:

Drink a full bottle → it becomes an empty bottle
Exchange numExchange empty bottles → get 1 new full bottle
Repeat until no more exchanges are possible

👉 Return the total number of bottles you can drink.

📌 Example

Input:

numBottles = 9
numExchange = 3

Process:

Start: 9 full bottles → drink them
drank = 9, empty = 9
Exchange: 9 empty → 3 full bottles
drink 3 → empty becomes 3
Exchange: 3 empty → 1 full bottle
drink 1 → empty becomes 1
Now: 1 empty bottle → cannot exchange anymore (needs 3)


Solution:
class Solution {
    fun numWaterBottles(numBottles: Int, numExchange: Int): Int {
        var full = numBottles
        var totalDrank = 0
        var empty = 0

        while(full > 0){
            totalDrank += full  // drank all
            empty += full // after drinking all bottles are empty

            full = empty / numExchange // calculate full 
            empty = empty % numExchange
        }

        return totalDrank
    }
}
